# x86_64 Initrd Installer Helpers

## Arch Linux `x86_64`

```bash
sudo ./generate_archlinux_x86_64_initrd_installer
./publish_archlinux_x86_64_initrd_installer
sudo ./test_archlinux_x86_64_initrd_installer
./portable_archlinux_installer
```

## CachyOS `x86_64_v3`

```bash
sudo ./generate_cachyos_v3_initrd_installer
./publish_cachyos_v3_initrd_installer
sudo ./test_cachyos_v3_initrd_installer
./portable_archlinux_installer
```

## CachyOS `x86_64_v4`

```bash
sudo ./generate_cachyos_v4_initrd_installer
./publish_cachyos_v4_initrd_installer
sudo ./test_cachyos_v4_initrd_installer
./portable_archlinux_installer
```

`portable_archlinux_installer` keeps the destination boot file names already used by the current system, and now picks the matching published Arch Linux or CachyOS installer artifacts automatically.

The test wrappers create a disposable copy of the corresponding built disk image, replace the boot kernel and initramfs in that copy with the generated installer artifacts, optionally wipe everything except `/boot`, and then launch the usual `../test_*` QEMU flow. Set `WIPE_ROOT=0` if you want to skip the wipe and just validate the boot handoff.

See [../../README](../../README) for the final image build/test/publish commands, and [../../common/initrd_installer/README](../../common/initrd_installer/README) for the shared initrd installer notes.
